  "prompt": "Does every dog has rabies?",
  "response": "No, not every dog has rabies. Rabies is a viral disease that affects the nervous system of mammals, including dogs, but it is not present in every dog. \n\nDogs can be vaccinated against rabies, and many are, especially in regions where the disease is more common. The disease is transmitted through the saliva of an infected animal, typically through a bite. \n\nIf you suspect a dog may have rabies, it's important to avoid contact with the animal and to report it to local animal control or health authorities. Symptoms of rabies in dogs can include aggression, excessive drooling, difficulty swallowing, and paralysis.",
